Pip 🥥 🌙 2023-05-03 11:55 AM
I'm very glad to hear you’re getting more sleep :D It could be true though, about using your phone. As someone definitely younger than you, if you can maybe try to use it a little less. Maybe read a chapter of a book or draw something 5 minutes before bed. Some people also say working out a bit/getting a little exercise in the evening help them sleep better. I think I know what you mean about waking up miserable though :( A couple things that help me are reading a book or going on Discord for a couple minutes to stimulate and wake up my brain for a couple minutes straight after waking up. Rosey suggested this and it helps! Also getting up fairly promptly after waking. Getting dressed or walking downstairs to get breakfast gets one moving and wakes you up even more. Lastly, though, habit. Keep at it. Getting to bed early at roughly the same time and waking up at roughly the same time will probably help you fall asleep and wake up faster. (edited)
